review_blob: Pours a light gold with white head. Aroma of pine citrus and yeast. Wonderful pine flavors. Finishes amazingly smooth.
Nice bourbon citrus aroma. Pours a hazy orange. The bourbon adds a very pleasant sweet flavor. Also picking up some candied Orange flavors.
Pours a gold in color with a thin whitish head. Aroma of hops, floral, slight citrus. Taste is hop and citrus some maltiness detected
Pours a nice copper color with off white head. Citrus nose. Nice balance of malt and hop.
beer_name: Odd Side Ales I Want My HTV

review_blob: Pours dark oil color with tan head. Aroma is chocolate, maple and booze. Very boozy taste semi bitter. Wonderful beer. Has a lot going on. Better as it warmed.
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series # 2: CBS (Canadian Breakfast Stout)

review_blob: Pours a nice dark oil color with a brown / khaki head. Aroma of dark malt, chocolate, and licorice. Taste is of malt chocolate and spice. Very smooth velvety mouth feel.
Pours a brownish red with a tan head. Aroma is certainly dank. Very hoppy and pine. Taste is very hop forward.
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series #13: reDANKulous Imperial Red IPA

review_blob: Pours gold with very little head. Aroma is of strawberry and bread. Taste is mildly sweet with a sourish strawberry flavor.
Pours a hazy gold. Aroma of citrus and grass. Taste is of citrus fruits and subtle tropical flavors. All in all one of the best DIPAs Ive ever had.
Pours dark black with nice creamy head. Aroma is sweet dark fruit and a slight booziness. Taste is of licorice and other dark fruits decent bitterness.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Bells Beer Camp Maillards Odyssey

review_blob: Pours a hazy Amber. Nose of banana, fruit and bread. Taste is of a malty breadiness with a slight sweetness.
Pours a dark gold color. Nose is strong in hops slightly tropical. Taste is of pine bitterness.
Pours a dark black with tan/beige head. Aroma of coffee and fruit. Taste is of booze and roastiness.
Pours a cloudy dirty red color with a tan head. Aroma is of bourbon and cider. Taste is of dark fruits and sweet on the tongue.

Aroma of blueberry and chocolate. Light creamy blue berry taste. Nice thick mouth feel.
Poors a dark black. Aroma of bourbon, and chocolate. Bourbon taste is pleasant but not overbearing. Overall a great beer. 2014 bottle.

review_blob: Pleasant aroma. Poors dark with a thin head. Hops are present but not overwhelming. Im not a huge black IPA fan but I place this at or near the top in that category.
